<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="PA-poly-rational-features">

	<statement>
		<p>
			Consider the rational function <m>r(x) = \frac{x^2 - 1}{x^2 - 3x - 4}</m>, and let <m>p(x) = x^2 - 1</m> (the numerator of <m>r(x)</m>) and <m>q(x) = x^2 - 3x - 4</m> (the denominator of <m>r(x)</m>).
		</p>

<!--
		<figure xml:id="F-rational-features-hole-1">
			<caption>A plot of <m>r(x) = \frac{x^2 - 1}{x^2 - 3x - 4}</m>.</caption>
			<image source="images/rational-features-hole-1" width="60%" />
		</figure>
-->

		<p>
			<ol label="a.">
				<li>
					<p>
						Reasoning algebraically, for what values of <m>x</m> is <m>p(x) = 0</m>?
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Again reasoning algebraically, for what values of <m>x</m> is <m>q(x) = 0</m>?
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Define <m>r(x)</m> in <em>Desmos</em>, and evaluate the function appropriately to find numerical values for the output of <m>r</m> and hence complete the following tables.
					</p>

					<sidebyside>
						<tabular>
							<row halign="center" bottom="minor">
								<cell><m>x</m></cell>
								<cell><m>r(x)</m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>4.1</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>4.01</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>4.001</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>3.9</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>3.99</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>3.999</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>							
						</tabular>

						<tabular>
							<row halign="center" bottom="minor">
								<cell><m>x</m></cell>
								<cell><m>r(x)</m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>1.1</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>1.01</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>1.001</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>0.9</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>0.99</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>0.999</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>							
						</tabular>

						<tabular>
							<row halign="center" bottom="minor">
								<cell><m>x</m></cell>
								<cell><m>r(x)</m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>-1.1</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>-1.01</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>-1.001</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>-0.9</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>-0.99</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>
							<row halign="center">
								<cell><m>-0.999</m></cell>
								<cell><m></m></cell>
							</row>							
						</tabular>						
					</sidebyside>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Why does <m>r</m> behave the way it does near <m>x = 4</m>?  Explain by describing the behavior of the numerator and denominator.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Why does <m>r</m> behave the way it does near <m>x = 1</m>?  Explain by describing the behavior of the numerator and denominator.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Why does <m>r</m> behave the way it does near <m>x = -1</m>?  Explain by describing the behavior of the numerator and denominator.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Plot <m>r</m> in <em>Desmos</em>.  Is there anything surprising or misleading about the graph that <em>Desmos</em> generates?
					</p>
				</li>				
			</ol>
		</p>
	</statement>

</exploration>